<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 2:50PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL MIFFLIN AND NORTH
CENTRAL JUNIATA COUNTIES THROUGH 315 PM EDT...
At 250 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lewistown, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Mcalisterville, Mexico, Alfarata, Walnut, Mifflintown, Port Royal,
Thompsontown, Mifflin, Maitland, East Salem and Wagner.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
